 your Python path, and that location must also contain a contexts.py module a templates folder with the templates (ending in .dj.html):</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> my_project/\r\n └── template_runner\r\n     ├── contexts.py\r\n     ├── template_runner.py\r\n     └── templates\r\n         ├── base_template_example.dj.html\r\n         └── index.dj.html\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">The contexts module should contain a single constant CONTEXTS which is a dictionary whose keys are the templates and whose values are the context dictionaries for those templates, for example:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> CONTEXTS = {\r\n\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'index.dj.html\'</span>: {\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Welcome to my Blog!\'</span>,\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'blog landing page\'</span>,\r\n     },\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact.dj.html\'</span>: {\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Contact Me\'</span>,\r\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact form\'</span>,\r\n     }\r\n\r\n }\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">One way to use this class is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">set up your directory structure as described above</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">make sure the template_runner directory is on your Python path</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">import the class: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">from template_runner import TemplateRunner</code></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">instantiate a TemplateRunner object: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">r = TemplateRunner()</code></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">process the templates: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">r.run()</code></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">TemplateRunner takes care of configuring basic Django settings for you, processes the templates with the contexts, and saves the output files (.html) alongside the templates:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">my_project/\r\n└── template_runner\r\n ├── contexts.py\r\n ├── template_runner.py\r\n └── templates\r\n   ├── base_template_example.dj.html\r\n   ├── index.dj.html\r\n   └── index.html\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">Once you set things up you can achieve a pretty fast workflow. I use Sublime Text 2 with the SublimeREPL package, so I don’t even have to leave the editor to run my templates. I just made this for my own personal use, but if you find it useful you can find the source code on <a href=\"https://github.com/jsonbrazeal/django-template-runner\">GitHub</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">What’s your preferred way to go about templating when building a small, mostly static site?</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"height: 0; font-size: 0em; padding: 0; margin: 0;\" title=\"MDH:PHA+SSBsb3ZlIHdvcmtpbmcgd2l0aCBEamFuZ28sIGJ1dCB5b3UgZG9uJ3QgbmVlZCB0aGUgZW50 aXJlIGZyYW1ld29yayBmb3IgZXZlcnkgd2ViIHByb2plY3QuIElmIEknbSBtYWtpbmcgYSBzbWFs bCwgbW9zdGx5IHN0YXRpYyBzaXRlLCBJIGxpa2UgdG8gc3RhcnQgd2l0aCBhIGJhc2UgaW5kZXgu aHRtbCBhbmQgQ1NTIGZ