0gb2YgcXVldWUgXTwvcD48cD4qIHN0cmluZyBtYW5pcHVs&lt;br /&gt;\r\nYXRpb24gd2l0aCBsaXN0czxicj4gYGBgcHl0aG9uPGJyPiBncm9jcyA9ICdtaWxrIGJyZWFkIGNv&lt;br /&gt;\r\nZmZlZSBtYXlvIGhhbSBjaGVlc2UnPGJyPiBncm9jcyA9IGdyb2NzLnNwbGl0KCk8YnI+IGdyb2Nz&lt;br /&gt;\r\nID0gWyctLScgKyBnIGZvciBnIGluIGdyb2NzXTxicj4gYGBgPC9wPjxwPiogY291bGQgZG8gc3R1&lt;br /&gt;\r\nZmYgaGVyZSBsaWtlIGVsaW1pbmF0ZSBkdXBsaWNhdGVzIG9yIHByb2Nlc3MgYWxsIHdvcmRzIHdp&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndGggYSBjZXJ0YWluIGNoYXJhY3RlcmlzdGljLCBldGMuPGJyPiBgYGBweXRob248YnI+IGdyb2Nf&lt;br /&gt;\r\nbGlzdCA9ICdcbicuam9pbihncm9jcyk8YnI+IHByaW50IGdyb2NfbGlzdDxicj4geF9kYXRhID0g&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWzEsIDQsIDIsIDUsIDYsIDMsIDgsIDRdPGJyPiB5X2RhdGEgPSBbMywgNSwgOCwgNCwgNSwgMSwg&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMiwgMl08YnI+IGRhdGFfcG9pbnRzID0gemlwKHhfZGF0YSwgeV9kYXRhKTxicj4geF95X2RhdGEg&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPSB6aXAoKmRhdGFfcG9pbnRzKTxicj4gYGBgPC9wPg==\">​</div>\r\n</div>','Python Lists','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2014-05-23 16:02:19','2014-05-23 16:02:19','',6,'http://jasonbrazeal.com/blog/?p=19',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2014-05-23 13:06:41','2014-05-23 17:06:41','<div class=\"markdown-here-wrapper\" data-md-url=\"http://jasonbrazeal.com/blog/wp-admin/post.php?post=15&amp;action=edit&amp;message=1\">\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">I love working with Django, but you don’t need the entire framework for every web project. If I’m making a small, mostly static site, I like to start with a base index.html and CSS files from <a href=\"http://html5boilerplate.com/\">html5bp</a> or <a href=\"http://getbootstrap.com/\">bootstrap</a>. Without using a templating system, the second page I made would violate one of <a href=\"https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/misc/design-philosophies/\">Django’s design philosophies</a> and a well-accepted good programming practice: DRY - Don’t Repeat Yourself. I know it might be easier to use PHP and that there are even standalone Python templating engines that can do this and more (see <a href=\"http://jinja.pocoo.org/\">Jinja</a>), but I wanted to try my hand at building a class that used Django’s machinery and allowed me to write Django templates and process them using context variables. So I came up with TemplateRunner.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">TemplateRunner can be run from the command line anywhere on your machine, but it does make a few assumptions. The template_runner.py module has to be in a location on your Python path, and that location must also contain a contexts.py module a templates folder with the templates (ending in .dj.html):</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> my_project/\n └── template_runner\n     ├── contexts.py\n     ├── template_runner.py\n     └── templates\n         ├── base_template_example.dj.html\n         └── index.dj.html\n</code></pre>\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">The contexts module should contain a single constant CONTEXTS which is a dictionary whose keys are the templates and whose values are the context dictionaries for those templates, for example:</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> CONTEXTS = {\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'index.dj.html\'</span>: {\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Welcome to my Blog!\'</span>,\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'blog landing page\'</span>,\n     },\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact.dj.html\'</span>: {\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Contact Me\'</span>,\n     <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact form\'</span>,\n     }\n }\n</code></pre>\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">One way to use this class is:</p>\n\n<ol style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">set up your directory structure as described above</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">make sure the template_runner directory is on your Python path</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">import the class: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">from template_runner import TemplateRunner</code></li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">instantiate a TemplateRunner object: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">r = TemplateRunner()</code></li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">process the templates: <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">r.run()</code></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">TemplateRunner takes care of configuring basic Django settings for you, processes the templates with the contexts, and saves the output files (.html) alongside the templates:</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">my_project/\n└── template_runner\n ├── contexts.py\n ├── template_runner.py\n └── templates\n   ├── base_template_example.dj.html\n   ├── index.dj.html\n   └── index.html\n</code></pre>\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">Once you set things up you can achieve a pretty fast workflow. I use Sublime Text 2 with the SublimeREPL package, so I don’t even have to leave the editor to run my templates. I just made this for my own personal use, but if you find it useful you can find the source code on <a href=\"https://github.com/jsonbrazeal/django-template-runner\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">What’s your preferred way to go about templating when building a small, mostly static site?</p>\n\n<div style=\"height: 0; font-size: 0em; padding: 0; margin: 0;\" title=\"MDH:PGRpdiBjbGFzcz0ibWFya2Rvd24taGVyZS13cmFwcGVyIiBkYXRhLW1kLXVybD0iaHR0cDovL2xv&lt;br /&gt; Y2FsaG9zdDo4MDA4L2Jsb2cvd3AtYWRtaW4vcG9zdC5waHA/cG9zdD0xNSZhbXA7YWN0aW9uPWVk&lt;br /&gt; aXQmYW1wO21lc3NhZ2U9MSI+PHA+PC9wPkkgbG92ZSB3b3JraW5nIHdpdGggRGphbmdvLCBidXQg&lt;br /&gt; eW91IGRvbid0IG5lZWQgdGhlIGVudGlyZSBmcmFtZXdvcmsgZm9yIGV2ZXJ5IHdlYiBwcm9qZWN0&lt;br /&gt; LiBJZiBJJ20gbWFraW5nIGEgc21hbGwsIG1vc3RseSBzdGF0aWMgc2l0ZSwgSSBsaWtlIHRvIHN0&lt;br /&gt; YXJ0IHdpdGggYSBiYXNlIGluZGV4Lmh0bWwgYW5kIENTUyBmaWxlcyBmcm9tIFtodG1sNWJwXSho&lt;br /&gt; dHRwOi8vaHRtbDVib2lsZXJwbGF0ZS5jb20vKSBvciBbYm9vdHN0cmFwXShodHRwOi8vZ2V0Ym9v&lt;br /&gt; dHN0cmFwLmNvbS8pLiBXaXRob3V0IHVzaW5nIGEgdGVtcGxhdGluZyBzeXN0ZW0sIHRoZSBzZWNv&lt;br /&gt; bmQgcGFnZSBJIG1hZGUgd291bGQgdmlvbGF0ZSBvbmUgb2YgW0RqYW5nbydzIGRlc2lnbiBwaGls&lt;br /&gt; b3NvcGhpZXNdKGh0dHBzOi8vZG9jcy5kamFuZ29wcm9qZWN0LmNvbS9lbi9kZXYvbWlzYy9kZXNp&lt;br /&gt; Z24tcGhpbG9zb3BoaWVzLykgYW5kIGEgd2VsbC1hY2NlcHRlZCBnb29kIHByb2dyYW1taW5nIHBy&lt;br /&gt; YWN0aWNlOiBEUlkgLSBEb24ndCBSZXBlYXQgWW91cnNlbGYuIEkga25vdyBpdCBtaWdodCBiZSBl&lt;br /&gt; YXNpZXIgdG8gdXNlIFBIUCBhbmQgdGhhdCB0aGVyZSBhcmUgZXZlbiBzdGFuZGFsb25lIFB5dGhv&lt;br /&gt; biB0ZW1wbGF0aW5nIGVuZ2luZXMgdGhhdCBjYW4gZG8gdGhpcyBhbmQgbW9yZSAoc2VlIFtKaW5q&lt;br /&gt; YV0oaHR0cDovL2ppbmphLnBvY29vLm9yZy8pKSwgYnV0IEkgd2FudGVkIHRvIHRyeSBteSBoYW5k&lt;br /&gt; IGF0IGJ1aWxkaW5nIGEgY2xhc3MgdGhhdCB1c2VkIERqYW5nbydzIG1hY2hpbmVyeSBhbmQgYWxs&lt;br /&gt; b3dlZCBtZSB0byB3cml0ZSBEamFuZ28gdGVtcGxhdGVzIGFuZCBwcm9jZXNzIHRoZW0gdXNpbmcg&lt;br /&gt; Y29udGV4dCB2YXJpYWJsZXMuIFNvIEkgY2FtZSB1cCB3aXRoIFRlbXBsYXRlUnVubmVyLjxicj4g&lt;br /&gt; PGJyPiBUZW1wbGF0ZVJ1bm5lciBjYW4gYmUgcnVuIGZyb20gdGhlIGNvbW1hbmQgbGluZSBhbnl3&lt;br /&gt; aGVyZSBvbiB5b3VyIG1hY2hpbmUsIGJ1dCBpdCBkb2VzIG1ha2UgYSBmZXcgYXNzdW1wdGlvbnMu&lt;br /&gt; IFRoZSB0ZW1wbGF0ZV9ydW5uZXIucHkgbW9kdWxlIGhhcyB0byBiZSBpbiBhIGxvY2F0aW9uIG9u&lt;br /&gt; IHlvdXIgUHl0aG9uIHBhdGgsIGFuZCB0aGF0IGxvY2F0aW9uIG11c3QgYWxzbyBjb2