CBldGMuPGJyPiBgYGBweXRob248YnI+IGdyb2Nf&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nbGlzdCA9ICdcbicuam9pbihncm9jcyk8YnI+IHByaW50IGdyb2NfbGlzdDxicj4geF9kYXRhID0g&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWzEsIDQsIDIsIDUsIDYsIDMsIDgsIDRdPGJyPiB5X2RhdGEgPSBbMywgNSwgOCwgNCwgNSwgMSwg&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMiwgMl08YnI+IGRhdGFfcG9pbnRzID0gemlwKHhfZGF0YSwgeV9kYXRhKTxicj4geF95X2RhdGEg&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPSB6aXAoKmRhdGFfcG9pbnRzKTxicj4gYGBgPC9wPg==\">​</div>\r\n</div>','Python Lists','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2014-06-01 10:47:06','2014-06-01 14:47:06','',6,'http://jasonbrazeal.com/blog/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(38,1,'2014-06-01 10:58:37','2014-06-01 14:58:37','<div class=\"markdown-here-wrapper\" data-md-url=\"http://jasonbrazeal.com/blog/wp-admin/post.php?post=6&amp;action=edit&amp;message=6\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">Welcome to my Python lists reference guide. The objective was to gather essential information on the list data type in one place with lots of examples. Please let me know what you think!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"create-lists-\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">create lists</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">create an empty list\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = []\r\nl = list()\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">lists can hold any combination or types of objects:\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [expression, ...]\r\nl = [[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>], [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>]]\r\nl = [student_1, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">56754</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">you can create a list by applying a function to every member of a sequence, called a list comprehension:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> l = [f(x) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> sequence]\r\n l = [x2 <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> range(<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">10</span>)]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">or by casting another sequence into a list type:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> l = list(sequence)\r\n l = list(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>)\r\n l = list((<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>))\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">assigning a variable to a list does not make a copy it:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> l1 = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>]\r\n l2 = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>]\r\n l2=l1 <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># now the list [1,2,3] is referenced by both l1 and l2. \r\n # the list [4,5,6] is an object with no references, no way to access it, so it will be garbage collected(?)</span>\r\n l1.pop() =\r\n l2 = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">use the list constructor or slicing notation to copy a list:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l2=list(l1)\r\nl2=l1[:] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># both of these make a copy of the list and assign its reference to l2</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">if you are iterating over a list in a loop which may require the list to be modified, consider iterating over a copy of the list instead(?)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"use-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">use lists</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">lists are organized internally (?) with an zero-based index pointing at each spot in the list\r\n[ diagram of list with index points, slice examples]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">you can use the slice notation to access one or more objects in the list</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>] = first item <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> list\r\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] = l[:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>]\r\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>] =\r\nl[-<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] = l[len(l)-<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] = last item <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> list\r\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>:len(l)] = l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>:]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">add a step parameter to get every second object, every third object, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l[::<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] =\r\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">8</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>] =\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">you can also use index to get the index of the first occurrence of the object</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l1.index(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>)\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">you can loop through lists using standard for-in loops</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> nums:\r\nprint(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'x= \'</span>, x)\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">use the enumerate function to get the indices too:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> i, x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> enumerate(nums):\r\nprint(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'i= \'</span>, i, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\' and x= \'</span>, x)\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">to test membership in a list, use the in operator for best performance</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">if</span> color <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'red\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'white\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'blue\'</span>]:\r\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'how patriotic!\'</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">to sort a list use sort to sort a list in place and sorted to return a sorted copy of the list while leaving the original untouched</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>]\r\nm = sorted(l) - l <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">is</span> still [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>]\r\nl.sort() - now both m <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">and</span> l are [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">other useful list functions</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> len(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns numbers of objects in list</span>\r\n l.count(x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns a number of times x occurs in list</span>\r\n max(l) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">and</span> min(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># return max/min of list (note on objects)</span>\r\n sum(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns sum of list</span>\r\n any(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># true if any true</span>\r\n all(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># true if all true</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<h2 id=\"modify-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">modify lists</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">list are a mutable data type, so they can be modified.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">slicing notation can be used to modify a list; just assign a portion of similar length to the slice\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>] = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'almost out\'</span>]\r\nl[:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'out\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'low\'</span>]\r\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">9</span>] = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">to add objects to a list use append, extend, or insert (modify list in place, return ???)\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l.append(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'extra\'</span>)\r\nl.extend[<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'extra\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'large\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'fries\'</span>]\r\nl.insert(i, x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># insert x at i</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">to remove objects from a list, use del, remove, or pop (modify list in place, return ???)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">del</span> l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete fourth item in the list, returns None?</span>\r\n <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">del</span> l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete fourth through sixth item in the list, returns None?</span>\r\n l.remove(x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># remove first occurrence of x in the list, returns None?</span>\r\n l.pop() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete and return last item in the list</span>\r\n l.pop(i) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete and return item at index i</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">you can use some operators on lists:\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>]\r\nl += [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>] - concatenation - like l.extend([<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>]) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">except</span> returns a new list\r\nl = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] * <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span> = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] + [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] + [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] - repetition\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"do-stuff-with-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">do stuff with lists</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">easily implement stack &amp; queue data structures using the methods described above\r\n[ diagram of stack ]\r\n——-list functions corresponding to diagrams——-\r\n[ diagram of queue ]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 0;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">string manipulation with lists</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">grocs = <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'milk bread coffee mayo ham cheese\'</span>\r\ngrocs = grocs.split()\r\ngrocs = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'--\'</span> + g <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> g <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> grocs]\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">could do stuff here like eliminate duplicates or process all words with a certain characteristic, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">groc_list = <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'\\n\'</span>.join(grocs)\r\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> groc_list\r\nx_data = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">8</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>]\r\ny_data = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">8</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>]\r\ndata_points = zip(x_data, y_data)\r\nx_y_data = zip(*data_points)\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style=\"height: 0; font-size: 0em; padding: 0; margin: 0;\" title=\"MDH:PHA+IyMgaW50cm88YnI+IFdl